external_knowledge:
- "Captains of the executive vessel" refers to active employees in the Executive department;
- "Voyages through the company's digital ports" refers to access events logged by employees;
- "Exceed a decade" means more than 10 access events;
- "Stations aboard the ship" refers to the office name where the employee works;
- "Ranks" refer to their job positions;
- "The name of the vessel they sail" refers to the department name.

- 'former employees' are those with a 'terminated' status;
- 'let go since the start of 2020' refers to termination dates on or after January 1, 2020;
- 'pay was adjusted' indicates changes in salary records;
- 'notes on how many times' means counting the occurrences of salary adjustments;
- 'sum of those adjustments' is the total cumulative change in salary.

- 'harbingers of financial wisdom' refers to employees with the position 'Accountant';
- 'departmental banners' metaphorically refers to the department names under which the accountants work;
- 'fortress of finance' metaphorically refers to the offices where the accountants are located.

sql:
SELECT position_id, position_name
FROM positions
WHERE salary_range = '$300,000 - $400,000';

SELECT name, age, salary
FROM employees
WHERE age > 30 AND CAST(REPLACE(salary, ',', '') AS REAL) > 50000;
